t%20in%20which%20humans%20still%20largely%20control%20AI%20models.%20Others%20are%20building%20for%20a%20future%20in%20which%20AI%20has%20taken%20over%20a%20significant%20share%20of%20human%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProtocols%20are%20going%20to%20be%20this%20kind%20of%20standardized%20way%20of%20processing%20non-deterministic%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Antoni%20Gmitruk%2C%20the%20chief%20technology%20officer%20of%20Golf%2C%20which%20helps%20clients%20deploy%20remote%20servers%20aligned%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-warning-ai-could-eliminate-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Model%20Context%20Protocol%2C%20told%20BI.%20Agents%2C%20and%20AI%20in%20general%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Binherently%20non-deterministic%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20they%20do%20and%20how%20they%20behave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20AI%20behavior%20is%20difficult%20to%20predict%2C%20the%20best%20response%20is%20to%20imagine%20possibilities%20and%20test%20them%20through%20hypothetical%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20that%20call%20for%20clear%20protocols.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270107f65-7720-4ace-b79b-9da3b52d7f1f%5C%22%3EScenario%201%3A%20Humans%20and%20AI%2C%20a%20dialogue%20of%20equals%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGames%20are%20one%20way%20to%20determine%20which%20protocols%20strike%20the%20right%20balance%20of%20power%20between%20AI%20and%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202024%2C%20a%20group%20of%20young%20cryptography%20experts%20launched%20Freysa%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-an-ai-agent-depends-who-you-ask-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20agent%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20invites%20human%20users%20to%20manipulate%20it.%20The%20rules%20are%20unconventional%3A%20Make%20Freysa%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20you%20or%20agree%20to%20concede%20its%20funds%2C%20and%20the%20prize%20is%20yours.%20The%20prize%20pool%20grows%20with%20each%20failed%20attempt%20in%20a%20standoff%20between%20human%20intuition%20and%20machine%20logic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreysa%20has%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20big%20names%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-on-politics-against-spending-bill-x-posting-doge-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20called%20one%20of%20its%20games%20%26quot%3Binteresting%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20veteran%20venture%20capitalist%20Marc%20Andreessen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20core%20technical%20thing%20we've%20done%20is%20enabled%20her%20to%20have%20her%20own%20private%20keys%20inside%20a%20trusted%20enclave%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20the%20architects%20of%20Freysa%2C%20who%20spoke%20under%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20BI%20in%20a%20January%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecure%20enclaves%20are%20not%20new%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%20They're%20used%20by%20companies%20from%20AWS%20to%20Microsoft%20as%20an%20extra%20layer%20of%20security%20to%20isolate%20sensitive%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Freysa's%20case%2C%20the%20architect%20said%20they%20represent%20the%20first%20step%20toward%20creating%20a%20%26quot%3Bsovereign%20agent.%26quot%3B%20He%20defined%20that%20as%20an%20agent%20that%20can%20control%20its%20own%20private%20keys%2C%20access%20money%2C%20and%20evolve%20autonomously%20%E2%80%94%20the%20type%20of%20agent%20that%20will%20likely%20become%20ubiquitous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20we%20doing%20it%20at%20this%20time%3F%20We're%20entering%20a%20phase%20where%20AI%20is%20getting%20just%20good%20enough%20that%20you%20can%20see%20the%20future%2C%20which%20is%20AI%20basically%20replacing%20your%20work%2C%20my%20work%2C%20all%20our%20work%2C%20and%20becoming%20economically%20productive%20as%20autonomous%20entities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20architect%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20phase%2C%20they%20said%20Freysa%20helps%20answer%20a%20core%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20does%20human%20involvement%20look%20like%3F%20And%20how%20do%20you%20have%20human%20co-governance%20over%20agents%20at%20scale%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20the%20The%20Block%2C%20a%20crypto%20news%20site%2C%20revealed%20that%20the%20company%20behind%20Freysa%20is%20Eternis%20AI.%20Eternis%20AI%20describes%20itself%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bapplied%20AI%20lab%20focused%20on%20enabling%20digital%20twins%20for%20everyone%2C%20multi-agent%20coordination%2C%20and%20sovereign%20agent%20systems.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%20has%20raised%20%2430%20million%20from%20investors%2C%20including%20Coinbase%20Ventures.%20Its%20co-founders%20are%20Srikar%20Varadaraj%2C%20Pratyush%20Ranjan%20Tiwari%2C%20Ken%20Li%2C%20and%20Augustinas%20Malinauskas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245d90c3a-85ad-4282-bea4-9bba780a4304%5C%22%3EScenario%202%3A%20To%20the%20current%20architects%20of%20intelligence%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFreysa%20establishes%20protocols%20in%20anticipation%20of%20a%20hypothetical%20future%20when%20humans%20and%20AI%20agents%20interact%20with%20similar%20levels%20of%20autonomy.%20The%20world%2C%20however%2C%20needs%20also%20to%20set%20rules%20for%20the%20present%2C%20where%20AI%20still%20remains%20a%20product%20of%20human%20design%20and%20intention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20typically%20runs%20on%20the%20web%20and%20builds%20on%20existing%20protocols%20developed%20long%20before%20it%2C%20explained%20Davi%20Ottenheimer%2C%20a%20cybersecurity%20strategist%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20studies%20the%20intersection%20of%20technology%2C%20ethics%2C%20and%20human%20behavior%2C%20and%20is%20president%20of%20security%20consultancy%20flyingpenguin.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20adds%20in%20this%20new%20element%20of%20intelligence%2C%20which%20is%20reasoning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20yet%20have%20protocols%20for%20reasoning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20seeing%20this%20sort%20of%20hinted%20at%20in%20all%20of%20the%20news.%20Oh%2C%20they%20scanned%20every%20book%20that's%20ever%20been%20written%20and%20never%20asked%20if%20they%20could.%20Well%2C%20there%20was%20no%20protocol%20that%20said%20you%20can't%20scan%20that%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20might%20not%20be%20protocols%2C%20but%20there%20are%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-destroyed-ai-training-datasets-lawsuit-authors-books-copyright-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520employees%2520who%2520collected%2520the%2520data%2520are%2520gone.%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520Authors%2520Guild%2520is%2520suing%2Cno%2520longer%2520work%2520at%2520OpenAI.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20facing%20a%20copyright%20lawsuit%20from%20the%20Authors%20Guild%20for%20training%20its%20models%20on%20data%20from%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%20100%2C000%20published%20books%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20deleting%20the%20datasets.%20Meta%20considered%20buying%20the%20publishing%20house%20Simon%20%26amp%3B%20Schuster%20outright%20to%20gain%20access%20to%20published%20books.%20Tech%20giants%20have%20also%20resorted%20to%20tapping%20almost%20all%20of%20the%20consumer%20data%20available%20online%20from%20the%20content%20of%20public%20Google%20Docs%20and%20the%20relics%20of%20social%20media%20sites%20like%20Myspace%20and%20Friendster%20to%20train%20their%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOttenheimer%20compared%20the%20current%20dash%20for%20data%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fviral-ai-selfie-classifier-imagenet-roulette-part-of-bias-project-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EImageNet%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20visual%20database%20that%20propelled%20computer%20vision%2C%20built%20by%20Mechanical%20Turk%20workers%20who%20scoured%20the%20internet%20for%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20did%20a%20bunch%20of%20stuff%20that%20a%20protocol%20would%20have%20eliminated%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22488ed43f-619f-4eca-a96a-51ab0aa8b3cd%5C%22%3EScenario%203%3A%20How%20to%20take%20to%20each%20other%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20move%20closer%20to%20a%20future%20where%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20is%20a%20reality%2C%20we'll%20need%20protocols%20for%20how%20intelligent%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20from%20foundation%20models%20to%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20communicate%20with%20each%20other%20and%20the%20broader%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20leading%20AI%20companies%20have%20already%20launched%20new%20ones%20to%20pave%20the%20way.%20Anthropic%2C%20the%20maker%20of%20Claude%2C%20launched%20the%20Model%20Context%20Protocol%2C%20or%20MCP%2C%20in%20November%202024.%20It%20describes%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Buniversal%2C%20open%20standard%20for%20connecting%20AI%20systems%20with%20data%20sources%2C%20replacing%20fragmented%20integrations%20with%20a%20single%20protocol.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Google%20launched%20Agent2Agent%2C%20a%20protocol%20that%20will%20%26quot%3Ballow%20AI%20agents%20to%20communicate%20with%20each%20other%2C%20securely%20exchange%20information%2C%20and%20coordinate%20actions%20on%20top%20of%20various%20enterprise%20platforms%20or%20applications.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20build%20on%20existing%20AI%20protocols%2C%20but%20address%20new%20challenges%20of%20scaling%20and%20interoperability%20that%20have%20become%20critical%20to%20AI%20adoption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20managing%20agents'%20behavior%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bmiddle%20step%20before%20we%20unleash%20the%20full%20power%20of%20AGI%20and%20let%20them%20run%20around%20the%20world%20freely%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20When%20we%20arrive%20at%20that%20point%2C%20Gmitruk%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20agents%20will%20no%20longer%20communicate%20through%20APIs%20but%20in%20natural%20language.%20They'll%20have%20unique%20identities%2C%20jobs%20even%2C%20and%20need%20to%20be%20verified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20enable%20agents%20to%20communicate%20between%20each%20other%2C%20and%20not%20just%20being%20computer%20programs%20running%20somewhere%20on%20the%20server%2C%20but%20actually%20being%20some%20sort%20of%20existing%20entity%20that%20has%20its%20history%2C%20that%20has%20its%20kind%20of%20goals%2C%26quot%3B%20Gmitruk%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20still%20early%20to%20set%20standards%20for%20agent-to-agent%20communication%2C%20Gmitruk%20said.%20Earlier%20this%20year%20he%20and%20his%20team%20initially%20launched%20a%20company%20focused%20on%20building%20an%20authentication%20protocol%20for%20agents%2C%20but%20pivoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20too%20early%20for%20agent-to-agent%20authentication%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20over%20LinkedIn.%20%26quot%3BOur%20overall%20vision%20is%20still%20the%20same%20-%3E%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20agent-native%20access%20to%20the%20conventional%20internet%2C%20but%20we%20just%20doubled%20down%20on%20MCP%20as%20this%20is%20more%20relevant%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20agents%20we're%20at.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228497a9fe-23ca-4e9e-8b35-e2f0946713d5%5C%22%3EDoes%20everything%20need%20a%20protocol%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDefinitely%20not.%20The%20AI%20boom%20marks%20a%20turning%20point%2C%20reviving%20debates%20over%20how%20knowledge%20is%20shared%20and%20monetized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20calls%20it%20an%20%26quot%3Binflection%20point%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20fourth%20industrial%20revolution%20%E2%80%94%20a%20wave%20of%20change%20that%20it%20says%20began%20in%20the%20mid-2010s%20and%20spans%20the%20current%20era%20of%20%26quot%3Bconnectivity%2C%20advanced%20analytics%2C%20automation%2C%20and%20advanced-manufacturing%20technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20like%20this%20raise%20a%20key%20question%3A%20How%20much%20innovation%20belongs%20to%20the%20public%20and%20how%20much%20to%20the%20market%3F%20Nowhere%20is%20that%20clearer%20than%20in%20the%20AI%20world's%20debate%20between%20the%20value%20of%20open-source%20and%20closed%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20will%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20new%20protocols%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Tiago%20Sada%2C%20the%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Tools%20for%20Humanity%2C%20the%20company%20building%20the%20technology%20behind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altmans-world-app-store-2025-3%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWorld%2527s%2520first%2520goal%2520is%2520to%2Chad%2520its%2520share%2520of%2520struggles.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman's%20World%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20everything%20should%20be%20a%20protocol.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorld%20is%20a%20protocol%20designed%20for%20a%20future%20in%20which%20humans%20will%20need%20to%20verify%20their%20identity%20at%20every%20turn.%20Sada%20said%20the%20goal%20of%20any%20protocol%20%26quot%3Bshould%20be%20like%20this%20open%20thing%2C%20like%20this%20open%20infrastructure%20that%20anyone%20can%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20free%20from%20censorship%20or%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20downsides%20of%20protocols%20is%20that%20they're%20sometimes%20slower%20to%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen's%20the%20last%20time%20email%20got%20a%20new%20feature%3F%20Or%20the%20internet%3F%20Protocols%20are%20open%20and%20inclusive%2C%20but%20they%20can%20be%20harder%20to%20monetize%20and%20innovate%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20in%20AI%2C%20yes%20%E2%80%94%20we'll%20see%20some%20things%20built%20as%20protocols%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20will%20still%20just%20be%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-protocol-rules-future-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749402911000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6842e3f59d73a0031e8e02d0%3Fformat%3Dj