ng%20my%20family%20identity.%20There%20were%20no%20feminist%20hesitations%20about%20the%20patriarchal%20expectation%20to%20subvert%20my%20identity%20for%20my%20husband's.%20I%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20Kelly%20Lee%20anymore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20husband's%20last%20name%20is%20O'Connell%2C%20and%20it%20was%20perfect.%20It%20wasn't%20weird%20or%20unattractive.%20When%20paired%20with%20my%20first%20name%2C%20it%20would%20have%20no%20unfortunate%20associations%20or%20sounds%20(think%20Lee%20Oswald%20or%20Lee%20Roy).%20And%20there%20was%20no%20way%20anyone%20would%20confuse%20it%20for%20a%20first%20name.%20I%20would%20never%20have%20to%20correct%20anyone%20about%20my%20name%20again.%20I%20would%20never%20be%20O'Connell%20Lee.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0bb6ec1-7482-425e-be66-bf477e5ff9ff%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20one%20gets%20it%20wrong%20now%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%2014%20years%20I've%20been%20married%2C%20I%20haven't%20had%20to%20correct%20someone%20about%20my%20name%20once.%20I%20am%20always%20Lee%2C%20never%20Kelly.%20My%20ears%20don't%20prick%20up%20when%20I%20hear%20%26quot%3BKelly%26quot%3B%20anymore%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20feel%20compelled%20to%20answer%20to%20any%20name%20besides%20my%20own.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStrangely%2C%20I%20received%20a%20letter%20addressed%20to%20Kelley%20Lee%20O'Connell%20two%20years%20ago.%20When%20I%20took%20my%20husband's%20name%2C%20I%20followed%20the%20convention%20of%20making%20my%20maiden%20name%20my%20middle%20name%2C%20mostly%20so%20I%20had%20a%20female%20name%20somewhere%20in%20there.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20saw%20that%20letter%2C%20I%20texted%20a%20photo%20to%20the%20high%20school%20friend%20who%20sat%20next%20to%20me%20in%20algebra%2C%20the%20one%20person%20who%20jokingly%20calls%20me%20Kelly%20Lee%20to%20this%20day.%20%26quot%3BShe%20does%20exist!%26quot%3B%20I%20exclaimed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221179%5C%