e%20how%20their%20bodies%20develop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20further%20understand%2C%20some%20people%20might%20have%20chromosomes%20usually%20linked%20to%20boys%20(called%20XY)%2C%20but%20their%20bodies%20look%20more%20like%20girls.%20Others%20might%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F287639%2Flessons-i-learned-from-my-brother-with-down-syndrome-sibling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echromosomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20usually%20linked%20to%20girls%20(XX)%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20certain%20body%20parts%20like%20a%20uterus.%20Some%20babies%20are%20born%20with%20body%20parts%20that%20aren%E2%80%99t%20clearly%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20know%20that%20being%20intersex%20is%3Cem%3E%20about%20the%20body%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20not%20about%20who%20someone%20feels%20inside%20or%20who%20they%20love.%20Some%20intersex%20people%20might%20also%20be%20transgender%2C%20meaning%20their%3Cem%3E%20inner%20sense%20of%20gender%3C%2Fem%3E%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20match%20how%20they%20were%20raised.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBut%20most%20intersex%20people%20aren%E2%80%99t%20transgender%2C%20and%20most%20transgender%20people%20aren%E2%80%99t%20intersex.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EOut%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20someone%20is%20out%2C%20it%20means%20they%20are%20open%20about%20being%20LGBTQ%2B%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20at%20home%20with%20family%2C%20at%20work%2C%20on%20social%20media%2C%20or%20in%20public%20spaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20being%20%E2%80%9Cout%E2%80%9D%20looks%20different%20for%20everyone.%20Some%20people%20might%20be%20out%20only%20to%20close%20friends%20or%20family%2C%20while%20others%20might%20speak%20openly%20in%20public%20or%20on%20platforms%20to%20inspire%20others%20or%20push%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Dutee%20Chand%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20sprinters%2C%20in%202019%2C%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20athlete%20to%20publicly%20come%20out%20as%20lesbian.%20She%20shared%20that%20she%20was%20in%20a%20same-sex%20relationship%2C%20despite%20knowing%20that%20it%20might%20bring%20criticism%20and%20pressure.%20However%2C%20by%20coming%20out%2C%20Dutee%20not%20only%20lived%20her%20truth%20but%20also%20gave%20courage%20to%20others%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESide%20note%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EComing%20out%20should%20not%20be%20confused%20with%20another%20term%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Eouting%2C%20which%20is%20the%20act%20of%20revealing%20another%20person%E2%80%99s%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity%20without%20their%20permission.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Sometimes%20it%20can%20be%20done%20based%20on%20rumours%20or%20assumptions.%20It%20is%20not%20considered%20appropriate%20even%20when%20the%20intentions%20are%20good%20because%20it%20simply%20takes%20away%20one%E2%80%99s%20choice%20and%20their%20control%20and%20can%20even%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20discrimination%2C%20rejection%20or%20worse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESay%20this%2C%20not%20that%3A%20terms%20you%20should%20avoid%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20thoughtful%2C%20inclusive%20language%20shows%20respect%20and%20helps%20create%20a%20world%20where%20everyone%20feels%20seen%20and%20valued%2C%20which%20we%20can%20all%20support.%20Here%20are%20some%20ways%20that%20we%20can%20keep%20in%20mind%20while%20writing%20about%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20and%20try%20our%20best%20to%20avoid%20ambiguous%20ideas%20and%20concepts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chermaphrodite%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Cintersex%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20hermaphrodite%20is%20outdated%20and%20considered%20offensive.%20It%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20someone%20has%20fully%20formed%20male%20and%20female%20reproductive%20systems%2C%20which%20is%20medically%20inaccurate%20and%20stigmatising.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20use%20%E2%80%9Cintersex%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20the%20respectful%20and%20accurate%20term%20for%20people%20born%20with%20physical%20sex%20traits%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20fit%20typical%20male%20or%20female%20categories.%20Also%2C%20avoid%20calling%20Hijras%20%E2%80%9Chermaphrodites%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F390947%2Fnoori-mohammad-abuse-transwoman-hiv-positive-india-children-shelter%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHijras%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20are%20a%20distinct%20cultural%20and%20gender%20identity%20in%20South%20Asia%20and%20should%20be%20recognised%20on%20their%20own%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Chomo%2C%E2%80%9D%20simply%20ask%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHomosexual%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20clinical%20term%20that%20feels%20cold%20and%20impersonal%20to%20many%20in%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community.%20The%20shortened%20version%20%E2%80%9Chomo%E2%80%9D%20is%20often%20used%20as%20a%20slur%20and%20is%20offensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20ask%20how%20people%20would%20like%20to%20be%20addressed.%20These%20terms%20are%20affirming%20and%20widely%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%20sex%2C%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Csex%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Crelationship%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20phrases%20like%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%20sex%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cgay%20sex%E2%80%9D%20can%20feel%20dehumanising%20and%20overly%20clinical.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20enough%20to%20say%20%E2%80%9Csex%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Crelationship%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Ccouple%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAlso%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20describe%20homosexuality%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccondition%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F288700%2Fadhura-starring-irrfan-khan-in-queer-film-gay-character-banned-by-censor-board%2F%5C%22%3E%20homosexua%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F288700%2Fadhura-starring-irrfan-khan-in-queer-film-gay-character-banned-by-censor-board%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elity%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccondition%E2%80%9D%20wrongly%20suggests%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20disorder%20or%20illness%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20cured.%20That%20idea%20has%20been%20disproven%20and%20rejected%20by%20medical%20and%20psychological%20experts%20around%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHomosexuality%20is%20simply%20a%20natural%20variation%20of%20human%20sexuality.%20So%2C%20just%20talk%20about%20it%20as%20an%20orientation%20or%20identity%2C%20not%20a%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Csexual%20preference%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20avoided%20because%20it%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20who%20someone%20is%20attracted%20to%20is%20just%20a%20choice%20like%20picking%20a%20favorite%20food.%20This%20idea%20has%20been%20used%20to%20support%20harmful%20beliefs%2C%20like%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfix%E2%80%9D%20or%20change%20someone%E2%80%99s%20sexuality%2C%20which%20is%20not%20only%20untrue%20but%20also%20very%20hurtful.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FTBI-featured-image-8-1749190165-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2